The post office&#8217;s Martie Gilchrist says they have seen a slight dip in letters to Santa Clause from children this year. CAPE TOWN The Post Office says children still send letters to Santa. There have been 500 in the Western Cape so far. The post office s Martie Gilchrist says they have seen a slight dip this year. Gilchrist says they have been hard at work to ensure Father Christmas receives all the letters. We send them off to Santa to make sure he receives them on time, we can t disappoint the kids. We fly out these letters e very night to the North Pole. 